1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d5
{ This is not very Benko-like, but clearly the best move here. } 3. Bg5
{ This is the Veresov opening. It's not that easy to tackle, because White usually gets quick development for strategic concessions. }
3... c5
{ I think this is the most aggressive move. Black just plays it like a Queen's Gambit Chigorin with reversed colors. }
4. e3 Nc6 5. dxc5 e6 6. Nf3 Bxc5
{ Is very comfortable for Black. The Knight is not well placed on c3 and Black has an extra centre pawn. You will castle short, play moves like h6, b6, Bb7. }
