[White "Deviations Move 2 (Tromp, London, Veresov etc)"]
[Black "Deviations Move 2 #15"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c3
{ White plays this to keep his options open with the c1 Bishop. } 2... c5
{ Now by far the most popular and logical move is 3 Nf3, which transposes to the next chapter via 1 d4 Nf6 2 Nf3 c5 3 c3. }
3. dxc5 e6 { quite like in the Slav or QGA this pawn cannot be kept. } 4. b4 a5
5. e3 axb4 6. cxb4 b6
{ and Black recovers the pawn with a good game. He's got good development and the a-pawn to play against. }
*

