[White "Deviations Move 2 (Tromp, London, Veresov etc)"]
[Black "Deviations Move 2"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4
{ The very solid London System. This is not an opening that you can expect to get a sharp position against. You rather have to keep the tension and be ready to play a long game. White's structure is just too sound to fall apart quickly. }
2... c5 { If possible, I like to attack the d-pawn in Benko fashion. } 3. d5
{ This is the most ambitious move for White, grabbing space.  Informational line. It is important to know that }
3... Qb6 4. Nc3 Qxb2 5. Bd2
{ Is a very risky gambit for Black to accept. I advise to avoid Qb6 here for that reason. We want to sac a pawn for the initiative with the Benko, not grab pawns and defend. }
