{ This is not very challenging. All moves to regain the pawn are fine. Besides the suggested move 3...Qa5 Black may also play 3...e6 or 3...Na6. }
3... Qa5+ 4. Nc3 { This seems most ambitious. } 4... Qxc5 5. e4 d6
{ With a Sicilian structure that seems fine for Black, especially considering that White started with 1 d4 /2 Nf3. If you dislike this idea there are good alternatives on move 3. }
