1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 c5 { This is the most Benko-like approach. } 3. c3
{ This move is actually not that easy to handle if you like a complicated game. Some approaches are quite equal, but also quite dull - while others are interesting, but also risky. Here's an overview. }
3... Qc7
{ This is my suggestion for a more combative game. Transposing to the Exchange Slav or playing e6 is more solid, but we want to mix it up with this repertoire - within reason. }
4. g3 g6 5. Bg2 Bg7 6. O-O O-O 7. Re1 d5 { and Black is fine again. } *

