{ A tough decision at this point for Black. The Queen sortie allows to recapture on f6 with the Queen and lends some cover to the queenside pawns. However take note that Black is falling more behind in development. }
5. c3
{ A good move by White. This is useful in most cases and makes Black decide on a setup. }
5... g6
{ I like this approach. Black is basically 'threatening' to play Bg7, allowing him to retake on f6 with a Bishop in the future. This makes taking on f6 now quite logical. }
6. Bxf6 Qxf6 7. e4 Qb6
{ The Queen again... but the game is quite closed at the moment, so Black gets away with it. This position is also appearing in the main line via 5 Bxf6 and discussed further there. }
