{ White certainly has some compensation, but Black should be fine. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "1 d4 Nf6 2 Nf3 c5"]
[Black "1 d4 Nf6 2 Nf3 c5 #24"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 c5 { This is the most Benko-like approach. } 3. d5 b5
{ Of course this is the move you want to play as a Benko fan. However you need to be aware that this line is somewhat risky for Black as he is not developing that quickly and weakens the queenside early on. }
4. Bg5 Qb6
{ A tough decision at this point for Black. The Queen sortie allows to recapture on f6 with the Queen and lends some cover to the queenside pawns. However take note that Black is falling more behind in development. }
5. Bxf6
{ This is the most popular move at this point. Black needs to move the Queen again, but he gains the Bishop pair. This long term asset is always good to have ! }
5... Qxf6 6. c3 g6
{ This is not that popular, but it seems like a good choice to me. I see no road to a white advantage. }
7. e4 Qb6 8. Nbd2 Bg7 9. a4 b4 10. Qc2 O-O 11. Bd3 d6 12. O-O Nd7
{ also looks fine for us. } *

