6. Ndb5 d5 7. Bf4 e5 8. cxd5 exf4 9. dxc6 bxc6 10. Qxd8+ Kxd8
{ A long forced sequence after 7 Bf4. Black has the worse structure, but the Bishop pair. f2 is also a soft spot, especially after White castles queenside. This is an unbalanced endgame that will often lead to interesting struggles. }
11. Nd4 Bd7 12. g3 Rb8 13. O-O-O Kc7 14. gxf4 Ng4
{ The important counterplay against f2. } 15. Ne4 Re8 16. f3 Ne3 17. Rd3 Nd5
{ And Black is fine again. He will get the pawn back or keep pressurizing White. }
*

