5. Nc3 e6
{ This is the best move here. g6 is the main alternative, but 6 e4 leads to the Maroczy Bind which is as far from the spirit of the Benko as you can imagine. Our move leads to lively piece play and more active chances for Black. }
6. Ndb5 d5 7. Bf4 e5 8. cxd5 exf4 9. dxc6 bxc6 10. Qxd8+ Kxd8
{ A long forced sequence after 7 Bf4. Black has the worse structure, but the Bishop pair. f2 is also a soft spot, especially after White castles queenside. This is an unbalanced endgame that will often lead to interesting struggles. }
11. Rd1+ Bd7 12. Nd6 Kc7 13. Nxf7 Rg8 14. Ne5 Rb8
{ Black is very active here. Note that Bf1 and Rh1 are not going to enter the game quickly. }
15. Nxd7 Nxd7 16. Rd2 Ne5 17. e3 fxe3 18. fxe3 Bb4 19. Be2 Bxc3 20. bxc3 Rb1+
