{ The simplest approach. } 5. e4 g6 6. Bxc4 d6 7. Nf3 Bg7 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1
{ This move and 9 h3 are very similar as White keeps the option of Na3 open. }
9... Ba6 10. Na3 Nfd7 11. Rb1 Bxc4 12. Nxc4 Nb6 13. Ne3 N8d7
{ Again this Nf6-d7-b6 manouvre worked quite well. Black is OK here. } *

