1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. Nc3
{ This nowadays is a rare line which enjoyed some popularity in the 70s and 80s. White intends to play e4 quickly. }
5... axb5 6. e4
{ This is the idea of 5 Nc3, leading to sharp play. To be quite frank: I think White's concept does not work and Black is better. However make no mistake: the play is very murky at times and can be tricky to handle. }
6... b4 7. Nb5 d6 8. Bf4 g5
{ This is the reason why the Sc3/e4 line has fallen out of fashion. } 9. Be3
Nxe4
{ If you can take a centre pawn without a clear refutation apparent you should do so. }
10. Bd3 Qb6
{ An important resource as confirmed by Stockfish. It has only been played once though, so we need to explore new ground here. }
11. Ne2 Bb7 12. Bxe4 Qxb5
{ Black is very much OK here. The engine gives Black a clear edge, but it is still very murky. }
*

