10. a3
{ The main move, trying to open up the queenside quickly. Note that Ba5 may cause havoc if Black takes it. }
10... e6
{ Extremely important move ! Taking on a3 instead leads to immediate disaster ! }
11. dxe6 Bxe6 12. axb4 Rxa1 13. Qxa1 d5
{ That is Black's concept: open the position against White's slow development. }
14. exd5 Nxd5 15. b5 Be7
{ Stockfish likes this even more than Nb4, which was OK in some games. } 16.
Ne2 O-O 17. Ng3 Re8
{ And White probably wonders at this point if f3 is such a good idea against the Benko...Black has an initiative for little material. }
*

