1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. bxa6 g6 6. Nc3 Bg7 7. e4 O-O 8. a7
Rxa7 9. Nf3 e6 10. Be2 exd5 11. exd5 d6 12. O-O Na6 13. Bb5
{ This move is a very serious test for Black's opening. White intends to place the Bishop on c6, supporting d5 and control vital squares in Black's camp, e8 in particular. }
13... Nc7
{ My suggestion to improve on the stem game L'Ami - Perunovic, Iceland 2015. Perunovic player Qb6 and got in trouble quickly. }
