{ I think this works, many other moves don't quite do. I don't want to swamp you with info lines if unneccessary. }
15. Bf4
{ This is the best move for White. Black intented to take on c6 and play Ra6, winning the Pawn back. Now d6 would be hanging in this line. }
15... Nh5 { initiating forcing play.Black has to be very concrete now. } 16.
Bg5 Qa8 17. Be7 { That looks grim for Black, but it works ultimately. } 17...
Rc8 18. Bxb7 Rxb7 19. Bxd6 { Otherwise Black will play Rb6 and pile up on d5. }
19... Rxb2 20. Rc1 Bxc3 21. Bxc7 Rxc7 22. Rxc3
{ 22 d6 first is just a move order twist. } 22... Nf4 23. d6 Rd7 24. Rxc5 Qa6
{ Two pawns down, but we are active enough yet again. } 25. a4 Rxd6 26. Qa1
Rdb6 27. a5 Rb8 { should also hold, Nd3 is an important idea. } *

