1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. bxa6 g6 6. Nc3 Bg7
{ This move has brought the Benko Gambit back on the map. Some years ago Black was suffering severly in the Main line Benko Accepted, so alternatives were needed quite badly. This new approach, starting with Bg7, is named after the Serbian GM Perunovic, who contributed a lot to its development. }
7. e4
{ The main move and the traditional reason why Bg7 was not viewed as a serious move some years ago. }
7... O-O 8. f4
{ This aggressive approach is actually quite risky for White. He creates many weaknesses in his camp and Black is not easily overrun as we will see. }
8... d6 9. Nf3 Qa5
{ The important move to remember. In the style of the Main line Perunovic White is irritated on the a5-e1 diagonal. }
10. Bd2 Bxa6 11. Be2 Nbd7 12. O-O Rfb8
{ Black has completed his traditional setup and is fine. Instead of 12. .. Rfb8 there also was c4 available, trying to use the d3 square. }
