1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. bxa6 g6 6. Nc3 Bg7
{ This move has brought the Benko Gambit back on the map. Some years ago Black was suffering severly in the Main line Benko Accepted, so alternatives were needed quite badly. This new approach, starting with Bg7, is named after the Serbian GM Perunovic, who contributed a lot to its development. }
7. e4
{ The main move and the traditional reason why Bg7 was not viewed as a serious move some years ago. }
7... O-O 8. Nf3 Qa5 9. Nd2
{ Breaking the pin, but it does not help development much. } 9... Bxa6 10. Be2
{ This is more testing then 10 Bxa6. } 10... d6 11. O-O Nfd7
{ Quite uncommon, but interesting here. Black directly attacks c3. } 12. Ndb1
{ This funny move is the engine suggestion after you let it calculate for a while. Black is still perfectly fine though. }
12... c4
{ There is no Knight coming to c6 anytime soon, so this is an interesting option. Not the only idea by any means, just developing is also fine. }
13. Qc2 Ne5 14. Bd2 Nbd7 { With nice compensation for Black. } *

