1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d5 b5 4. cxb5 a6 5. bxa6 g6 6. Nc3
{ Informational line: } 6... Bxa6
{ This is the traditional move. Let's a have a quick look at the line that is causing Black problems. }
7. e4 Bxf1 8. Kxf1 d6 9. g3 Bg7 10. Kg2 O-O 11. Nf3 Nbd7 12. a4
{ This is the line that causes Black problems. White aims to put a Knight on b5 and keep it there. This piece is a roadblock for Black's queenside play. Please keep this motif in mind: if White establishes a Knight on b5 in the Benko accepted it will be a huge issue if there is no way to get rid of it. }
